[1mNAME[0m[m
       tr - translate or delete characters[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
       [1mtr[0m [[4mOPTION[24m]... [4mSET1[24m [[4mSET2[24m][m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       Translate, squeeze, and/or delete characters from standard input, writing to stan‐[m
       dard output.[m
[m
       [1m-c[0m, [1m-C[0m, [1m--complement[0m[m
              use the complement of SET1[m
[m
       [1m-d[0m, [1m--delete[0m[m
              delete characters in SET1, do not translate[m
[m
       [1m-s[0m, [1m--squeeze-repeats[0m[m
              replace each sequence of a repeated character that is listed  in  the  last[m
              specified SET, with a single occurrence of that character[m
[m
       [1m-t[0m, [1m--truncate-set1[0m[m
              first truncate SET1 to length of SET2[m
[m
       [1m--help[0m display this help and exit[m
[m
       [1m--version[0m[m
              output version information and exit[m
[m
       SETs  are  specified as strings of characters.  Most represent themselves.  Inter‐[m
       preted sequences are:[m
